The study should take you around 7 minutes to complete.
This survey will be best displayed on a laptop or desktop computer.

We are data science graduate students at the University of California, Berkeley. We are researching how people perceive political bias and factualness in the titles of articles from major publications when presented in a reddit news feed.  There are two main types of articles: news and opinion.

column2: A news article contains information about current events where the author is expected strive for objectivity.
An opinion article reflects the author's opinion about the subject and includes editorials, columns and op-eds.

column1: You will be presented titles recently posted in the reddit r/politics news feed and asked to answer some questions about them.  All of your responses will be kept completely confidential.
To be eligible for this study you must:

column2: Be able to read and comprehend English fluently
Possess a basic understanding of liberal vs. conservative viewpoints in the United States

column1: If you choose to participate,  you acknowledge that you meet the eligibility requirement.
